Single-database configuration for Flask.

Apply Migrations (If Using Flask-Migrate)
If you're using Flask-Migrate, follow these steps to create and apply migrations:

a. Initialize Migrations
Run this command to initialize the migrations directory (if not already done):

flask db init

b. Create Migration Script
Generate a new migration script based on your models:

flask db migrate -m "Create post table"

c. Apply Migrations
Apply the migration to create the table in the database:

flask db upgrade
